eans and standard deviations</em></p></div>
          </div>
        </div></div><div class=3D"default-content-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"mean--=
median--mode"><strong>2. Mean =3D median =3D mode</strong></h3><p>The mean,=
 median and mode are three ways to measure the center of a set of data valu=
es. For a true normal distribution, these three are identical. In practice,=
 your data is likely to be nearly normal. The mean, median and mode are lik=
ely to be very close to each other, but not identical.</p><p>
